		  	 <table width=85% border=0 cellpadding=5 cellspacing=0 align=center>
  <tr>
    <td bgcolor='0e024d' class='spti2'>THE DISCIPLINE OF MIGHTY STRIKE</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td class='db'><b>Class:</b>&nbsp;Warrior</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td class='db'><b>Level obtained:</b>&nbsp;54</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td class='db'><b>Duration:</b>&nbsp;10 seconds.</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td class='db'><b>Re-Use Delay:</b>&nbsp;60 minutes.</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td class='db'><b>Re-Use Delay at Level 60:</b>&nbsp;54 minutes.</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td class='db'><b><u>Discipline Description:</u></b><P>When using this discipline all landed attacks will automatically be either Critical Hits or Crippling Blows.  This discipline lasts for 10 seconds and has a base reuse time of 60 minutes.  The reuse time for this discipline will decrease as the warrior gains additional levels.</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td>  <table border='0' width='100%' cellspacing='0' cellpadding='5'>
    <tr>
      <td width='95%' align='left' valign='top' colspan=2 bgcolor='#000066' class='spti2'>DISCIPLINE COMMENTS</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td width='95%' align='left' valign='top' colspan=2 class='db'><span class='dbti'>CHAMPION</span><b>, By Bgal</b><br><br>I am a 54 Warrior, so let me set this straight.  There are 2 possible times to use this skill:

When not berserk:  You do all critical hits and essentially double your damage for 10 seconds.

When berserk (taken below 35% health by a melee blow, or after being hit in melee when below 35% health):  You do triple damage with all hits and stun creatures very briefly - very usefull for when things are running away and you are low on health.

As far as weapon choice, whatever is normally your most effective weapon will be the most effective weapon for this discipline.  The weigted axe is not it.

I use the ability with Quickening cast by an Enchanter, and I ask the Cleric in the group to start a Complete heal as soon as they see me go berserk.  Complete heal takes 10 seconds to cast, and once you go berserk, you stay that way for a few seconds even after healed so you have plenty of time to use the discipline.  The weapons I use are:

Main hand: 9/18
Off hand: 11/24

Typically in that 10 seconds I hit between 12 and 25 times for between 900 and 1800 damage, with hits anywhere from 30 to 150s.<br><hr size='1'></td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td width='95%' align='left' valign='top' colspan=2 class='db'><span class='dbti'>NO...</span><b>, By Etadanik</b><br><br>You don't have to be below 15% to use this discipline, in what I observed.  It is a nasty discipline to use, probably reserved for the desperate times against a dragon.  You probably don't want to use this as a part of your daily routine as a tank.  

<p>Remember, Critical Strike and Crippling Blows always do more damage than an average hit.  If all the blows you land are crippling blows/critical strikes, imagine the possibilities of using two 1h high damage weapons.  I mean one of those things that do 11/22 delay.  You would be doing ALOT of damage during 10 seconds plus stunning the foe with crippling blows.  Extremely useful vs. Vox or Nagafen.

<p>And to the guy who says a necro pet can almost solo Vox... Wow you must be making a joke in sarcasm, or else you're a level 1 warrior who has read all the newsboards and taken them as facts.  A level 53 necro pet actually tanks less than a level 49 necro pet, and can barely solo a zol knight one on one.
<br><hr size='1'></td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td width='95%' align='left' valign='top' colspan=2 class='db'><span class='dbti'>THIS ROCKS</span><b>, By Quale birdmaster 50 warrior</b><br><br>This skill is amazing, I have seen this go off a couple of times now, each time the level 54 warrior has done over 1500 damage in the 10 seconds. With a 2h weapon he did about 1300 damage. This skill is damn good.<br><hr size='1'></td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td width='95%' align='left' valign='top' colspan=2 class='db'><span class='dbti'>WELL...</span><b>, By Anonymous</b><br><br>Ok, lets go through this. you are talking about slow 2 handed weapons - slower means less hits in 10 seconds. however try this - get the 2 fastest weapons you can find (you must be good with the skill of the weapon) get an enchanter friend and get &#34;swift like the wind&#34; cast on you. now use it! double attack and dual wield+super faster = a whole buncha dmg.<br><hr size='1'></td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td width='95%' align='left' valign='top' colspan=2 class='db'><span class='dbti'>WHY SLOW 2 HANDERS?</span><b>, By Kinlaar</b><br><br>it seems as though an executioner's axe is the most common example of a warrior's weapon here.  i doubt that a warrior who can use this skill will have an exe axe.  most likely a lvl 50+ warrior will have at least a mith 2hander, which is much faster than an exe axe, and with permanent haste, or have a sword dropped by a god/dragon, etc. and if that doesn't have haste then he will probably have a haste item.  That's not even including one hand slashing weapons.<br><hr size='1'></td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
